       mailcheck  checks  for  the existence of mail. Whenever it
       finds some, it prints the You have mail message  on  stan-
       dard output.

       If  there is no mail, it prints No mail on standard error.

       mailcheck is commonly used in a user's  $HOME/.profile  as
       follows:  mailcheck 2>/dev/null This prints a message when
       there is mail, and is otherwise silent.

